51
00:19:37,722 --> 00:19:39,084
Why do a condo conversion ordinance?

52
00:19:39,764 --> 00:19:49,813
This is, like I said, it's just one strategy, but it's a way of making sure that the city has more control and has a seat at the table when the conversion of rental units to condominiums happens in a city.

53
00:19:49,833 --> 00:19:54,937
And we know that in Medford, that's already been happening quite a lot, especially in Hillside and South Medford.

54
00:19:55,844 --> 00:20:01,407
A condo conversion provides a really fantastic profit opportunity for for-profit developers and for house flippers.

55
00:20:02,728 --> 00:20:13,253
And we've seen this, but especially if corporations and for-profit flippers that aren't rooted here in Medford, that kind of have no business in Medford except for extracting property from these conversions.

56
00:20:13,313 --> 00:20:21,978
If they're going to profit from housing in our community, we should make sure that that transaction gives something back to our community as well, to individual tenants who are displaced.

57
00:20:22,715 --> 00:20:25,876
